name: C. MEX Cycle
input: InputEach test contains multiple test cases. The first line contains the number of test cases $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \le t \le 10^4$$$). The description of the test cases follows. The first and only line of each test case contains three integers $$$n$$$, $$$x$$$, $$$y$$$ ($$$3 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$$$, $$$1 \le x < y \le n$$$).It is guaranteed that the sum of $$$n$$$ over all test cases does not exceed $$$2 \cdot 10^5$$$.
output: OutputFor each test case, output $$$n$$$ space-separated non-negative integers $$$a_1, a_2, \ldots, a_n$$$ ($$$0 \le a_i \le 10^9$$$) on a line that satisfy the condition in the statement. If there are multiple solutions, print any of them. It can be proven that under the problem constraints, a solution with $$$0 \le a_i \le 10^9$$$ always exists.
